LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - ASIA (10): AFGHANISTAN (LAGHMAN) CATTLE, FIRST REPORT, WOAH
********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 30 Jun 2022
Source: WOAH-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/report-info?reportId=56500


Lumpy skin disease [LSD] virus (inf. with), Afghanistan
-------------------------------------------------------
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 29 May 2022
Confirmed: 29 Jun 2022
Reported: 30 Jun 2022
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence in the country
Causal agent: lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to the whole country.

Outbreak location 1: Qarghayi, Laghman
Started: 29 May 2022
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 12 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 1 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Disease infected cattle in one district of Laghman province. The surveillance system information also shows the occurrence of the disease in another part of the province, we will share in the weekly follow-up report.

Control measures at event level
Control measures applied, domestic: ante and post-mortem inspections, control of vectors, movement control, selective killing and disposal, slaughter, surveillance outside the restricted zone, surveillance within the restricted zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Diagnostic and Research Laboratory, AFG (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Outbreaks / Test date / Result
Cattle / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 1 / 29 May to 29 Jun 2022 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[An outbreak of lumpy skin disease was recently detected in the province of Kandahar, see ProMED posting 20220620.8703967.

Laghman is one of the 34 provinces of Afghanistan, located in the eastern part of the country. Kandahar is located in the south of the country. A map of the provinces of Afghanistan can be seen at https://www.worldatlas.com/upload/b2/68/b4/provinces-of-afghanistan-map.png. - Mod.CRD

ProMED map:
Afghanistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8704213,137]
